'''Tatsushima Meoyanomikoto Shrine''' (たつしまめおやのみことじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Nakata-chō (Komatsushima)|Q11366737|WD=Q11366737|lt=Nakata-chō|1=Chūdenchō}}, {{ill|lt=Komatsushima|Q823493|WD=Q823493|1=Komatsushima, Tokushima}}, {{ill|lt=Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734|WD=Q160734|1=Tokushima Prefecture}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
With '''Tatsushima Meoyanomikoto''' (たつしまめおやのみこと) as principal deity, it also {{ill|lt=merged enshrines|Q11412524|WD=Q11412524|1=Co-Enshrinement}} {{ill|lt=Emperor Ōjin|Q317997|WD=Q317997|1=Emperor Ōjin}}.
[[File:Tatsushimajinjya distant view.JPG|thumb|Distant view of Tatsushima Shrine]]

Tatsushima Meoyanomikoto is often identified with Haniyasu-hime-no-Mikoto, though there are differing opinions. "Tatsushima" (or "Tate-shima") was also at times read "Takeshima," and in early modern gazetteers appears as "Takeshima Daimyōjin."

=== Shrine crest ===
* Dakii-ne

=== History ===
Though the founding era is unknown, it is known to be very old because it is an {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Engishiki shrine|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286|lt=Shikinaisha}} and because shrine tradition at {{ill|lt=Hanifu Shrine|Q11555577|WD=Q11555577|1=Hanifu Shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Takashima, Shiga|Q845794|WD=Q845794|1=Takashima, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|WD=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}, says that in {{ill|lt=741|Q23597|WD=Q23597|1=741}} (Tenpyō 13), Haniyama-hime-no-Mikoto was invited from '''Tatsushima Meoyanomikoto Shrine''' in {{ill|lt=Naka District|Q1156492|WD=Q1156492|1=Naka District, Tokushima}}, {{ill|lt=Awa Province|Q907457|WD=Q907457|1=Awa Province (Tokushima)}} (present-day {{ill|lt=Komatsushima|Q823493|WD=Q823493|1=Komatsushima, Tokushima}}, {{ill|lt=Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734|WD=Q160734|1=Tokushima Prefecture}}).

It was also called Tatsushima Daimyōjin and Takeshima Daimyōjin. In Nakata-chō where this shrine stands, there are {{ill|lt=kofun clusters|Q11411019|WD=Q11411019|1=Kofun cluster}} from the early {{ill|lt=Kofun period|Q459939|WD=Q459939|1=Kofun period}}, suggesting rule by local {{ill|lt=powerful clans|Q84066|WD=Q84066|1=Gōzoku}} since ancient times. Former village shrine.

